uge (bore diameter)|12 gauge]] [[shotgun]]. He shot and killed a custodian and wounded the assistant principal, a teacher and a police officer before being arrested. Ledger was later sentenced to 57 years in prison, but died there on December 24, 2011 due to Natural Causes.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1994/11/08/us/man-fires-shotgun-in-school-killing-one-and-injuring-3.html |title=Man Fires Shotgun In School, Killing One and Injuring 3 |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1994-11-08 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 5, 1995\n| [[Washington, District of Columbia]], United States\n| ..., 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Antar A. Hall is shot to death by a 14-year-old boy at the entrance of Cardozo High School.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost/access/18589823.html?dids=18589823:18589823&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+06%2C+1995&author=Paul+Duggan%3B+Wendy+Melillo&pub=The+Washington+Post+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=Student+Fatally+Shot+at+Cardozo+High%3B+D.C.+Police+Say+Suspect+Is+Youth%2C+14&pqatl=google|title=Student Fatally Shot at Cardozo High; D.C. Police Say Suspect Is Youth, 14|first=Paul|last=Duggan|date=January 6, 1995}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 1995\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| ..., 15\n| \n| 2 injured\n| A 15-year-old [[Garfield High School (Seattle, Washington)|Garfield High School]] student left school during the day, after a conflict with another student, and returned with his grandfather's 9mm semiautomatic handgun. He invented on frightening the other student, but a personal confrontation lead to him opening fire. He wounded two students, the student he was fighting with, as well as another female student who was a bystander.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/the-shooter/Content?oid=13491|title=The Shooter|newspaper=The Stranger|author=Eli Sanders|date=2003-03-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1995\n| [[Charlotte Amalie, United States Virgin Islands]], United State