48, conducted a massacre at Tala'i Private School, in the Asbahi township. Armed with an illegally obtained [[AK-47|Kalashnikov]] [[assault rifle]], he waited for the headmistress and killed her by shooting her in the head. After killing a cafeteria worker and injuring a bus driver who came to help, he entered the school building and walked from classroom to classroom, shooting indiscriminately at teachers and students. Subsequently he went to nearby Musa Bin Nusayr School where he continued his rampage, that left a total of six people dead and 12 others wounded, before he himself was injured and arrested. al-Nazari was ultimately convicted of murder and was executed by firing squad just six days after the massacre.<ref name=Independent>[http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_/ai_n14090868 Yemeni father's school slaughter], ''[[The Independent]]'' (March 31, 1997)</ref>\n|-\n| April 28, 1997\n| [[Seabrook, New Jersey]], United States\n| Peter Henriques, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old student Nielsa Mason is beaten to death by fellow 16-year-old student Peter Henriques inside the boys\u2019 locker room at [[Cumberland Regional High School]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/04/30/nyregion/girl-16-slain-in-school-and-a-classmate-is-arrested.html |title=Girl, 16, Slain in School and a Classmate Is Arrested |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1997-04-30 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Melody |last=Petersen}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/05/01/nyregion/motive-a-puzzle-in-a-high-school-murder.html |title=Motive a Puzzle in a High School Murder |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1997-05-01 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Barry |last=Bearak}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 5, 1997\n| [[Z\u00f6bern]], Austria\n| Helmut Z., 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 15-year-old student Helmut Z. shot and killed a teacher at his school with a revolver he had stolen from his father, after she had intervened when he tried to rape a girl. He also shot and injured another te