iesha|last=Lofing |author2=Ryan Lillis |author3=Dorothy Korber |title=Hostage situation ends at California high school.|date=2007-09-28|url =http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-33008402_ITM|work=[[The Sacramento Bee]]|accessdate = 2009-04-21}}</ref><ref name=\"cbs13929\">{{cite news|title=Arrest Made After Hostages Held At Oroville School|date=2007-09-29|publisher=[[KOVR|CBS 13]]|url =http://cbs13.com/local/Las.Plumas.High.2.483133.html|accessdate = 2009-04-21}} {{Dead link|date=November 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> Wright was tried and convicted in adult court on charges of [[false imprisonment]] and firearms offenses and was sentenced to 22 years in prison in January 2008.<ref name=\"kcra11708\">{{cite news|title=Las Plumas Shooter Sentenced To 22 Years|date=2008-01-17|publisher=[[KCRA]]|url=http://www.kcra.com/news/15076509/detail.html|accessdate=2009-04-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320064322/http://www.kcra.com/news/15076509/detail.html|archivedate=2012-03-20}}</ref><ref name=\"sfgate20108\">{{cite news|title=Mom wants Oroville school shooter's guilty plea reversed |date=2008-02-01 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/n/a/2008/02/01/state/n142539S66.DTL&type=health |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090705040125/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fn%2Fa%2F2008%2F02%2F01%2Fstate%2Fn142539S66.DTL&type=health |archive-date=2009-07-05 |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |accessdate=2009-05-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"sfgate21508\">{{cite news|title=Teen wants hostage conviction tossed|date=2008-02-15|agency=[[Associated Press]]|url =http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2008/02/15/BASBV3759.DTL|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|accessdate = 2009-05-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 10, 2007\n| [[Cleveland]],<br>[[Ohio]],<br>United States\n| Asa H. Coon, 14\n| 1 dead\n| 4 injured\n| [[SuccessTech Academy shooting]]. 14-year-old student Asa Coon, report